---

## 2. Description of Service

The Live Attendance Tracking App is a workforce management tool that provides:

- PIN-based employee authentication
- Clock-in and clock-out functionality
- GPS location tracking during work hours
- Real-time location updates to the company's Odoo server
- Attendance record management

This App is intended for use by authorized employees of organizations that have implemented the Odoo ERP system with the attendance tracking module.

---

## 3. User Eligibility

To use this App, you must:

- Be an authorized employee or contractor of an organization using this App
- Have received valid login credentials (PIN) from your employer
- Be at least 18 years of age or the legal age of employment in your jurisdiction
- Have a compatible Android device with GPS capabilities

---

## 4. User Account and Security

- You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your PIN
- You must not share your login credentials with any other person
- You are responsible for all activities that occur under your account
- You must notify your employer immediately of any unauthorized use of your account
- Your employer reserves the right to disable your access at any time

---

## 5. Location Data Collection and Use

By using this App, you acknowledge and consent to the following:

### 5.1 Location Tracking

- The App collects your GPS location when you clock in
- Location updates are sent to the company server approximately every minute while you are clocked in
- Location tracking stops when you clock out
- Background location tracking continues even when the App is minimized or closed, but only while you are clocked in

### 5.2 Purpose of Location Data

Location data is collected for:

- Verifying attendance at designated work locations
- Tracking field employee movements during work hours
- Generating attendance and location reports for management
- Ensuring employee safety and accountability

### 5.3 Data Storage

- Location data is transmitted to and stored on your organization's Odoo server
- Your employer is the data controller and determines data retention policies
- Location data is not shared with third parties by the App

---

## 6. User Responsibilities

When using this App, you agree to:

- Provide accurate attendance information
- Not manipulate or falsify location data
- Not use GPS spoofing or mock location applications
- Keep your device's location services enabled during work hours
- Ensure your device has adequate battery and internet connectivity
- Clock in and out honestly and accurately
- Comply with your employer's attendance policies

---

## 7. Prohibited Activities

You are prohibited from:

- Using the App for any unlawful purpose
- Attempting to bypass or manipulate location tracking
- Sharing your PIN with others or using another person's PIN
- Reverse engineering, decompiling, or disassembling the App
- Interfering with or disrupting the App's functionality
- Using automated systems or software to interact with the App
- Attempting to gain unauthorized access to company servers

---

## 8. Device Requirements and Permissions

The App requires the following permissions to function properly:

| Permission | Purpose |
|------------|---------|
| Location (All the time) | Required for GPS tracking during work hours |
| Internet Access | Required for data synchronization with the server |
| Background Processing | Required for continuous location updates |
| Foreground Service | Required to maintain tracking when the App is minimized |

You must grant these permissions for the App to function. Denying permissions may result in the App not working correctly.

